Description: Jubilance is a sisterhood of women on a mission to make PMS mood swings a thing of the past.
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Kathy Cash and her husband Alan ran a small family business selling a lesser-known nutritional supplement called oxaloacetate. They sold oxaloacetate mostly to doctors, who recommended it to their patients for a number of different symptoms. Doctors began to report that their female patients were experiencing a curious “side effect” after taking oxaloacetate: life-changing relief from PMS mood swings. Alan was pleasantly surprised to hear the news, but then went about his day. As a woman, Kathy knew this wasn’t just a nice side benefit, it was a monumental discovery could transform the lives of millions of women. They both knew the cause needed a woman champion, so Kathy struck out on her own to launch a new brand, Jubilance, with a mission to make PMS mood swings a thing of the past. After multiple placebo-controlled clinical trials showing Jubilance provides dramatic reductions in PMS-related anxiety, gloominess, irritability and stress, Jubilance has become one of the fastest-growing women’s health brands in the U.S.

Full Description: Woop!Wear is a growing clothing company specializing in active wear made primarily of alpaca fibers.  Woop!Wear’s mission is to introduce a wider public to the benefits of alpaca-based clothing through their high-quality, lightweight active wear. Alpaca-based active wear is an ideal product for the environmentally conscious consumer who wishes to buy minimally processed, natural fibers and to support sustainable products and businesses. Furthermore, the alpaca-based materials produced by Woop!Wear have been proven to be as lightweight as wool, yet provide more insulation, breathability, and moisture-wicking. Woop!Wear provides consumers interested in outdoor sports or cold-weather activities with an appropriate, comfortable, and eco-friendly line of clothing to help them do what they love to do. The company reaches these consumers through wholesale operations and, on a smaller scale, through direct consumer sales on the company’s website. While more alpaca-based products have appeared on the market in recent years, Woop!Wear maintains a competitive edge because it uses a higher percentage of alpaca in its blends and because it offers lightweight active wear.
